Now I can see the critical difference between the local code and what Sourcegraph showed. The **local code** (which is what matters) has a different structure. Let me verify the key difference.

In the **Sourcegraph version** (latest default branch), the v38 `processPanelsV38` function at lines 115-131 has this structure:

```go
// Process defaults.custom if it exists
if defaults, ok := fieldConfig["defaults"].(map[string]interface{}); ok {
    if custom, ok := defaults["custom"].(map[string]interface{}); ok {
        // Migrate displayMode ...
    }
}
// Update any overrides referencing the cell display mode
// This must be called regardless of whether defaults.custom exists
migrateOverrides(fieldConfig)
```

But in the **local code** (lines 115-136), the structure is:

```go
defaults, ok := fieldConfig["defaults"].(map[string]interface{})
if !ok {
    continue  // <-- SKIPS the entire panel including overrides!
}

custom, ok := defaults["custom"].(map[string]interface{})
if !ok {
    continue  // <-- SKIPS the entire panel including overrides!
}

// Migrate displayMode to cellOptions
...

// Update any overrides referencing the cell display mode
migrateOverrides(fieldConfig)
```

This is the regression. Let me now verify local code to be sure this is the actual state.

